    "body": "I was watching this since I had the same issue. Unfortunately, this didn't work for me.\r\nHere is my config:\r\n\r\n```\r\n# Prompt format\r\nformat = \"\"\"\r\n$directory\\\r\n$git_branch\\\r\n$git_commit\\\r\n$git_state\\\r\n$git_metrics\\\r\n$git_status\\\r\n${env_var.YAZI_ID}\\\r\n$line_break\\\r\n$character\"\"\"\r\n\r\n# Replace the \"âťŻ\" symbol in the prompt with \"âžś\"\r\n[character]\r\nsuccess_symbol = \"[âžś](bold green)\"\r\nerror_symbol = \"[âś–](bold red)\"\r\nvicmd_symbol = \"[âž¤](bold green)\"\r\n\r\n[git_status]\r\nahead = 'â¬†'\r\nbehind = 'â¬‡'\r\n\r\n# https://github.com/starship/starship/issues/6246\r\n[env_var.YAZI_ID]\r\nvariable = 'YAZI_ID'\r\ndefault = ''\r\nformat = '([yazi]($style))'\r\nstyle = 'bold blue'\r\n```\r\n(it is intended to just show `[yazi]` instead of the value of the variable)\r\n\r\nEven if the variable is present, it does not show anything.\r\nEscaping the `[]` like so `format = '(\\[yazi\\]($style))'` also does not work.\r\n\r\n\r\nJust as a counter example, if I use the custom module however, it works:\r\n```\r\n# Prompt format\r\nformat = \"\"\"\r\n$directory\\\r\n$git_branch\\\r\n$git_commit\\\r\n$git_state\\\r\n$git_metrics\\\r\n$git_status\\\r\n${custom.yazi}\\\r\n$line_break\\\r\n$character\"\"\"\r\n\r\n# Replace the \"âťŻ\" symbol in the prompt with \"âžś\"\r\n[character]\r\nsuccess_symbol = \"[âžś](bold green)\"\r\nerror_symbol = \"[âś–](bold red)\"\r\nvicmd_symbol = \"[âž¤](bold green)\"\r\n\r\n[git_status]\r\nahead = 'â¬†'\r\nbehind = 'â¬‡'\r\n\r\n[custom.yazi]\r\nwhen = 'test -n \"$YAZI_ID\"'\r\nformat = '[\\[yazi\\]]($style)'\r\nstyle = 'bold blue'\r\n```\r\n\r\n(I can not use the `format = '(...)'` here though, since this will also show nothing)\r\n\r\nWhat am I missing here regarding the configuration for the `env_var` module?",
